CHAPTER 3
PLAYING FORMAT
See Rules

#rule("6", "TO SCORE A POINT, TO WIN A SET AND THE MATCH")[
]

#subrule("6.1", "TO SCORE A POINT")[
]
  #r("6.1.1")[Point A team scores a point:]
  #r("6.1.1.1")[by successfully landing the ball on the opponent’s court; D9 (14)]
  #r("6.1.1.2")[when the opponent team commits a fault;]
  #r("6.1.1.3")[when the opponent team receives a penalty.]
  #r("6.1.2")[Fault A team commits a fault by making a playing action contrary to the rules (or by violating them in some other way). The referees judge the faults and determine the consequences according to the rules:]
  #r("6.1.2.1")[if two or more faults are committed successively, only the first one is counted;]
  #r("6.1.2.2")[if two or more faults are committed by opponents simultaneously, a DOUBLE FAULT is called and the rally is replayed. D9 (23)]
  #r("6.1.3")[Rally and completed rally A rally is the sequence of playing actions from the moment of the service hit by the server until the ball is out of play. A completed rally is the sequence of playing actions which results in the award of a point. This includes: –  the award of a penalty –  loss of service for a service hit made after the time-limit. 8.1, 8.2, 12.2.2.1, 12.4.4, 22.3.2.2]
  #r("6.1.3.1")[If the serving team wins a rally, it scores a point and continues to serve.]
  #r("6.1.3.2")[If the receiving team wins a rally, it scores a point and it must serve next.]

#subrule("6.2", "TO WIN A SET")[
  A set (except the deciding 3rd set) is won by the team which first scores
  21 points with a minimum lead of two points. In the case of a 20-20 tie,
  play is continued until a two-point lead is achieved (22-20; 23-21; etc).
  D9 (9)
]

#subrule("6.3", "TO WIN THE MATCH")[
]
  #r("6.3.1")[The match is won by the team that wins two sets. D9 (9)]
  #r("6.3.2")[In the case of a 1-1 tie, the deciding 3rd set is played to 15 points with a minimum lead of 2 points.]

#subrule("6.4", "DEFAULT AND INCOMPLETE TEAM")[
]
  #r("6.4.1")[If a team refuses to play after being summoned to do so, it is declared in default and forfeits the match with the result 0-2 for the match and 0-21, 0-21 for each set.]
  #r("6.4.2")[A team that does not appear on the playing court on time is declared in default. 6.4.1]
  #r("6.4.3")[A team that is declared INCOMPLETE for the set or for the match, loses the set or the match. The opponent team is given the points, or the points and the sets, needed to win the set or the match. The incomplete team keeps its points and sets. 6.2, 6.3, 7.3.1 For FIVB, World and Official Competitions, whenever the Pool Play format is implemented, Rule 6.4 above may be subject to modifications as stated in the Specific Competition Regulations issued by the FIVB in due time, establishing the modality to be followed for treating the default and incomplete team cases.]

#rule("7", "STRUCTURE OF PLAY")[
]

#subrule("7.1", "THE TOSS")[
  Before the official warm up, the 1st referee conducts the toss to decide
  upon the first service and the sides of the court in the first set.
]
  #r("7.1.1")[The toss is taken in the presence of the two team captains, where appropriate.]
  #r("7.1.2")[The winner of the toss chooses: EITHER]
  #r("7.1.2.1")[the right to serve or to receive the service, OR]
  #r("7.1.2.2")[the side of the playing court. The loser takes the remaining choice.]
  #r("7.1.2.3")[In the second set the loser of the toss in the first set will have the choice of 7.1.2.1 or 7.1.2.2. A new toss will be conducted for the deciding set.]

#subrule("7.2", "OFFICIAL WARM-UP SESSION")[
  Prior to the match, if the teams have previously had another playing
  court at their disposal, they will have a 3-minute official warm-up period
  at the net; if not, they may have 5 minutes.
]

#subrule("7.3", "TEAM LINE-UP")[
]
  #r("7.3.1")[Both players of each team must always be in play. 4.1.1]

#subrule("7.4", "POSITIONS")[
  At the moment the ball is hit by the server, each team must be within its
  own court (except the server).
]
  #r("7.4.1")[The players are free to position themselves. There are NO determined positions on the court.]

#subrule("7.5", "POSITIONAL FAULT")[
]
  #r("7.5.1")[There are NO positional order faults.]

#subrule("7.6", "SERVICE ORDER")[
]
  #r("7.6.1")[Service order must be maintained throughout the set (as determined by the team captain immediately following the toss).]
  #r("7.6.2")[When the receiving team has gained the right to serve, its players “rotate” one position.]

#subrule("7.7", "SERVICE ORDER FAULT")[
]
  #r("7.7.1")[A service order fault is committed when the service is not made according to the service order. The team is sanctioned with a point and service to the opponent. D9 (13)]
  #r("7.7.2")[The scorer(s) must correctly indicate the service order and correct any incorrect server prior to the whistle for service.]
